# ============================================================
# F5 — ANTHROPIC SELF-POSTMORTEM CONFIRMS HARNESS-IS-LEVER (L4 max)
# ============================================================
#
# Anthropic April 23 2026 official postmortem on Claude Code degradation:
# 6 weeks of degraded responses (March 4 - April 20) traced to 3 changes:
#   (1) default reasoning effort changed HIGH → MEDIUM on March 4 (to
#       reduce UI-frozen latency)
#   (2) prompt caching bug March 26 (session-based caching)
#   (3) verbosity system prompt April 16 ("≤25 words between tool calls,
#       ≤100 final" — internal testing showed "no regressions")
# All three are HARNESS-LEVEL (config + caching + system prompt).
# Anthropic API was UNAFFECTED — the MODEL didn't degrade. Only the
# harness around it did. Direct vendor-adversarial admission.
#
# Plus Stella Laurenzo (AMD Senior Director AI) audit of 6,852 sessions
# + 234,000 tool calls: reasoning depth fell, reasoning loops, "simplest
# fix not correct fix" — practitioner L4 corroboration.
#
# Grade: S=3 production at scale, C=3 specific change/dates/numbers,
# D=3 vendor admits, I=3 max-adversarial (vendor publishing harm to own
# product reputation), V=3 multiple outlets confirm. Score: 15/15 max L4.
# U-filter: U1=2 strong (vendor public-admits "your premise was right"),
# U2=2 mechanism named with dates, U3=2 falsifiable ship-resolved-on-
# v2.1.116 (verifiable), U4=2 corroborated independently. U=8/8 max.
lemma f5_anthropic_april_23_postmortem_harness_changes_caused_degradation_l4_max_2026
  proves True
  by audit anthropic-engineering-april-23-postmortem-fetched-2026-05-03

