# ============================================================
# F7 — HARNESS-WRAPS-MODEL CONVERGENT EVOLUTION (4 new traditions)
# ============================================================
#
# CHE pass 4 found 4 unrelated traditions independently re-deriving
# the harness-wraps-model pattern (orthogonal to facts/22's parallel-
# aggregation traditions; this is about WRAPPING/control-plane,
# not voting/aggregation):
#
#   T11 — Distributed robotic networks (Bullo/Cortés/Martínez 2009):
#         decentralized control with neighboring topology described by
#         undirected interaction graph; convergence guarantees via
#         priority-based arbitration.
#   T12 — Biological homeostasis in collective robotic systems
#         (Springer 2010): immune-system-inspired feedback for
#         steady-state in massively-changing environments.
#   T13 — Central Pattern Generators (CPG) in robotics (arxiv 1509.02417):
#         oscillator coupling provides stability single units lack.
#   T14 — Distributed cooperative systems control theory (OSTI):
#         hierarchical coordination wraps local subsystems for
#         system-level guarantees.
#
# Plus existing facts/22's 10 traditions for parallel-aggregation +
# facts/14's MoA / multi-agent literature = 14+ orthogonal traditions
# converging on harness-wraps-or-aggregates-model. Per CLAUDE.md (b)
# convergent-evolution-without-contact criterion fires strongly.
#
# Grade: L3 academic. U=7-8/8 (this CHE finding wasn't widely surfaced
