# ============================================================
# F8 — SMALL-SPECIALIST + RAG OUTPERFORMS FRONTIER (cost lever)
# ============================================================
#
# CHE pass 5 findings:
#   - Gartner 2026: task-specific small models will outnumber general-
#     purpose 3:1 by 2027
#   - ACE (Agentic Context Engineering) on AppWorld leaderboard:
#     smaller open-source model MATCHES top production agent on overall
#     average and SURPASSES on harder test-challenge split. +10.6% on
#     agents, +8.6% on finance — gains from CONTEXT not model size.
#   - "RAG-powered models significantly outperform long-context models
#     in answer accuracy regardless of frontier LLM choice" (PNNL)
#   - Caveat (atom 0015 honest): models <7B have CONTEXT-UTILIZATION
#     limitation; deploying RAG at this scale "can lead to net negative
#     trade-off under standard evaluation" (arxiv 2603.11513)
#
# Implication for cheapcode COST AXIS: cheap-tier (deepseek-v4-flash
# is much-larger-than-7B; gpt-5-mini also) + RAG context engineering
# can replace some frontier dispatch entirely. The 7B caveat doesn't
# bind cheapcode's cheap-tier choices. This is a NEW cost-reduction
# lever beyond just voter-pattern.
#
# Grade: L3 + L4 mix. U=7/8.
lemma f8_small_specialist_plus_rag_matches_frontier_at_lower_cost_above_7b_threshold_l3_l4
  proves True
  by audit ace-appworld-pnnl-gartner-fetched-2026-05-03

# ============================================================
# F9 — PARALLEL-DISPATCH REDUCES WALLCLOCK (latency lever)
# ============================================================
#
# CHE pass 6 findings:
#   - "Parallel tool calling reduces decoding tokens AND LLM generation
#     latency... wall-clock time is reduced" (arxiv 2602.07359)
#   - "Mediator's synthesis work is the SEQUENTIAL FRACTION" in agent
#     systems — Amdahl's law applies
#   - Voice agent end-to-end latency: 50-70% reduction via unified
#     architecture (Deepgram); sub-100ms TTFA new baseline 2026
#   - Memory ops OFF the inference path (background worker pattern)
#   - Frameworks with fewer layers between you and LLM = lower latency
#
# Implication for cheapcode LATENCY AXIS:
#   (a) cheapcode-witness v1x ALREADY parallel-dispatches witnesses ✓
#   (b) synthesizer (gpt-5-mini, ~tokens-budget-bounded) IS the
#       sequential fraction; minimize synthesizer work to reduce p99
#   (c) atom 0007 anti-fab is cheap; keep synthesizer that way
#   (d) memory/conversion-factor estimator should run BACKGROUND, not
#       block inference loop (verify in M3.34 implementation)
#
# Grade: L3 + L5. U=6/8.
lemma f9_parallel_dispatch_minimal_synthesizer_off_path_memory_reduces_latency_l3_l5
  proves True
  by audit parallel-tool-calling-amdahl-deepgram-fetched-2026-05-03

